 ] Create `docs/docs/architecture/workloadmanager.md` with:\n36:   - [ ] Sandbox lifecycle management description (create, delete, GC)\n37:   - [ ] Kubernetes API interactions (CRDs, Pods, Secrets)\n38:   - [ ] Health check and metrics endpoints documentation\n39:   - [ ] Endpoint table: `/sandboxes` POST, `/sandboxes/:id` GET/DELETE, `/health/live`, `/health/ready`\n40: \n41: ### PicoD Component\n42: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/architecture/picod.md` with:\n43:   - [ ] Local code execution daemon description (sidecar role)\n44:   - [ ] Workspace isolation and sanitization explanation\n45:   - [ ] File operations documentation (upload, download, list)\n46:   - [ ] Code execution timeout management\n47:   - [ ] Endpoint details: `/api/execute`, `/api/files`\n48: \n49: ### Agentd Component\n50: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/architecture/agentd.md` with:\n51:   - [ ] Controller-runtime architecture explanation\n52:   - [ ] Idle threshold detection logic\n53:   - [ ] Leader election for singleton controller\n54:   - [ ] Cleanup workflow steps\n55:   - [ ] Configuration parameters: `--idle-threshold`, `--check-interval`, `--leader-election`\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ## Phase 3: Data Flow Documentation (REQ-003)\n60: \n61: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/architecture/data-flow/` directory\n62: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/architecture/data-flow/sandbox-creation.md` with:\n63:   - [ ] Step-by-step flow diagram: SDK → Router → WorkloadManager → K8s API → Router → SDK\n64:   - [ ] Timeout and retry behavior notes for each step\n65: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/architecture/data-flow/code-execution.md` with:\n66:   - [ ] Execution flow: Client → Router → PicoD → Router → Client\n67:   - [ ] Error handling scenarios (timeout, sandbox not ready, invalid auth)\n68: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/architecture/data-flow/session-routing.md` with:\n69:   - [ ] Session state maintenance explanation (Redis/Valkey mappings)\n70:   - [ ] Session key structure documentation (`session:<id>`)\n71:   - [ ] Session TTL and cleanup logic\n72:   - [ ] Session lifecycle states: Created, Active, Expired, Terminated\n73: \n74: ---\n75: \n76: ## Phase 4: Python SDK API Documentation (REQ-004)\n77: \n78: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/api/sdk-python/` directory\n79: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/api/sdk-python/overview.md` with:\n80:   - [ ] Installation instructions (`pip install agentcube-sdk`)\n81:   - [ ] Quick start code example\n82:   - [ ] SDK architecture diagram (Control Plane vs Data Plane)\n83:   - [ ] Version compatibility table\n84: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/api/sdk-python/code-interpreter-client.md` with:\n85:   - [ ] Class initialization parameters (`router_url`, `workload_manager_url`, `jwt_token`)\n86:   - [ ] `execute_code(language, code, timeout)` method signature, return type, examples\n87:   - [ ] `execute_command(command)` method signature and examples\n88:   - [ ] `upload_file(path, content)` method documentation\n89:   - [ ] `download_file(path)` method documentation\n90:   - [ ] `list_files()` method documentation\n91:   - [ ] `create_session()` and `stop_session()` methods\n92:   - [ ] Exception types for each method\n93: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/api/sdk-python/agent-runtime-client.md` with:\n94:   - [ ] Client initialization parameters\n95:   - [ ] `invoke_agent(agent_name, input_data)` method\n96:   - [ ] Session management for agent invocations\n97:   - [ ] Response format documentation\n98:   - [ ] Examples: basic invocation, session reuse, error handling\n99: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/api/sdk-python/exceptions.md` with:\n100:   - [ ] `AgentCubeError` (base exception)\n101:   - [ ] `CommandExecutionError` with attributes (`exit_code`, `stderr`)\n102:   - [ ] `SessionError`, `DataPlaneError`, `AuthenticationError`\n103:   - [ ] Exception hierarchy diagram\n104:   - [ ] Example code for catching and handling exceptions\n105: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/api/sdk-python/sessions.md` with:\n106:   - [ ] Session creation and configuration options\n107:   - [ ] Context manager pattern example\n108:   - [ ] Explicit session management example\n109:   - [ ] Session timeout behavior\n110: \n111: ---\n112: \n113: ## Phase 5: Go Client API Documentation (REQ-005)\n114: \n115: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/api/client-go/` directory\n116: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/api/client-go/overview.md` with:\n117:   - [ ] Go module installation (`github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`)\n118:   - [ ] Kubernetes client-go integration explanation\n119:   - [ ] CRD types (`AgentRuntime`, `CodeInterpreter`)\n120:   - [ ] Kubernetes version compatibility\n121: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/api/client-go/clientset.md` with:\n122:   - [ ] `NewForConfig(config *rest.Config)` function signature\n123:   - [ ] `NewForConfigOrDie(config)` panic variant\n124:   - [ ] Clientset interface methods (`RuntimeV1alpha1()`, `Discovery()`)\n125:   - [ ] Code example for clientset construction\n126: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/api/client-go/agent-runtime-crud.md` with:\n127:   - [ ] Create, Get, List, Update, UpdateStatus, Delete methods\n128:   - [ ] DeleteCollection, Patch, Watch methods\n129:   - [ ] Type signatures, parameter descriptions, return types\n130:   - [ ] Code examples for each CRUD operation\n131: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/api/client-go/code-interpreter-crud.md` with:\n132:   - [ ] Complete CRUD method documentation mirroring AgentRuntime structure\n133:   - [ ] Code examples for all operations\n134: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/api/client-go/informer.md` with:\n135:   - [ ] `SharedInformerFactory` construction\n136:   - [ ] `Start(stopCh)` and `Shutdown()` methods\n137:   - [ ] `WaitForCacheSync(stopCh)` for cache synchronization\n138:   - [ ] AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter informers\n139:   - [ ] Lister interface usage patterns\n140:   - [ ] Code example for informer setup and usage\n141: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/api/client-go/testing.md` with:\n142:   - [ ] `NewSimpleClientset()` for unit testing\n143:   - [ ] Adding reactors for custom behavior\n144:   - [ ] Object tracking and retrieval\n145:   - [ ] Watch simulation in tests\n146:   - [ ] Test example code snippet\n147: \n148: ---\n149: \n150: ## Phase 6: CRD Schema Documentation (REQ-006)\n151: \n152: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/architecture/crd/` directory\n153: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/architecture/crd/agent-runtime.md` with:\n154:   - [ ] Full YAML schema example\n155:   - [ ] Spec fields: `replicas`, `image`, `resources`, `env`, `volumeMounts`\n156:   - [ ] Status fields: `phase` (Running, Pending, Failed), `conditions`, `podName`\n157:   - [ ] Validation rules and default values\n158: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/architecture/crd/code-interpreter.md` with:\n159:   - [ ] Full YAML schema example\n160:   - [ ] Spec fields: `language`, `timeout`, `workspaceSize`\n161:   - [ ] Status fields: `sessionID`, `podIP`, `lastExecutionTime`\n162:   - [ ] Example YAML manifest\n163: - [ ] Document API group and version: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n164: \n165: ---\n166: \n167: ## Phase 7: Configuration Documentation (REQ-007)\n168: \n169: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/deployment/config/` directory\n170: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/deployment/config/router-config.md` with:\n171:   - [ ] Flag documentation: `--port`, `--store-addr`, `--store-type`, `--max-concurrent`, `--enable-tls`\n172:   - [ ] Environment variable overrides: `PORT`, `STORE_ADDR`, `STORE_TYPE`\n173:   - [ ] Default values, valid ranges, usage descriptions, example command lines\n174: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/deployment/config/workloadmanager-config.md` with:\n175:   - [ ] Flags: `--addr`, `--gc-interval`, `--kubeconfig`, HTTP timeouts\n176:   - [ ] Example deployment YAML with configuration\n177: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/deployment/config/picod-config.md` with:\n178:   - [ ] Flags: `--port`, `--workspace`, `--auth-enabled`, `--max-exec-time`, `--max-file-size`\n179:   - [ ] Security configuration best practices\n180: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/deployment/config/agentd-config.md` with:\n181:   - [ ] Flags: `--idle-threshold`, `--check-interval`, `--max-concurrent-cleanup`, `--leader-election`\n182:   - [ ] Leader election configuration explanation\n183: \n184: ---\n185: \n186: ## Phase 8: Deployment Documentation (REQ-008)\n187: \n188: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/deployment/` directory (if not exists)\n189: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/deployment/prerequisites.md` with:\n190:   - [ ] Kubernetes version requirements (≥1.24)\n191:   - [ ] Required cluster resources (CPU, memory)\n192:   - [ ] Redis/Valkey deployment instructions\n193:   - [ ] Helm 3 installation instructions\n194:   - [ ] kubectl configuration steps\n195: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/deployment/helm-installation.md` with:\n196:   - [ ] Helm chart location\n197:   - [ ] Installation command: `helm install agentcube ./manifests/helm/agentcube`\n198:   - [ ] Required values configuration (Redis, JWT, namespace)\n199:   - [ ] Optional values table\n200:   - [ ] Post-installation verification steps\n201: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/deployment/multi-namespace.md` with:\n202:   - [ ] Separate namespace deployment explanation\n203:   - [ ] Cross-namespace communication configuration\n204:   - [ ] RBAC requirements for multi-namespace access\n205:   - [ ] YAML examples for namespace-scoped deployment\n206: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/deployment/security.md` with:\n207:   - [ ] TLS certificate configuration for Router\n208:   - [ ] JWT signing key management\n209:   - [ ] RBAC configuration for WorkloadManager\n210:   - [ ] Network policies for pod isolation\n211:   - [ ] Secret management best practices\n212: \n213: ---\n214: \n215: ## Phase 9: Examples and Tutorials (REQ-009)\n216: \n217: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/examples/` directory\n218: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/examples/overview.md` with:\n219:   - [ ] Examples overview and index\n220: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/examples/pcap-analyzer.md` with:\n221:   - [ ] PCAP analyzer application description\n222:   - [ ] Architecture diagram (LangChain + AgentCube)\n223:   - [ ] Setup and deployment instructions\n224:   - [ ] Code walkthrough for key components\n225:   - [ ] Link to `example/pcap-analyzer/` source\n226: - [ ] Update `docs/docs/getting-started/first-sandbox.md` (if exists) or create with:\n227:   - [ ] Step 1: Install AgentCube via Helm\n228:   - [ ] Step 2: Configure Python SDK connection\n229:   - [ ] Step 3: Create first sandbox session\n230:   - [ ] Step 4: Execute Python code\n231:   - [ ] Step 5: Upload and download files\n232:   - [ ] Step 6: Clean up session\n233:   - [ ] Code examples and expected output for each step\n234: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/examples/langchain-tutorial.md` with:\n235:   - [ ] LangChain tool wrapper implementation\n236:   - [ ] Agent workflow with code execution\n237:   - [ ] Session management in multi-turn conversations\n238:   - [ ] Error handling patterns\n239:   - [ ] Runnable code snippets\n240: \n241: ---\n242: \n243: ## Phase 10: Navigation and Cross-References (REQ-010)\n244: \n245: - [ ] Update `docs/sidebars.ts` with:\n246:   - [ ] `architecture` sidebar category with autogenerated directory\n247:   - [ ] `api` sidebar with `sdk-python` and `client-go` categories\n248:   - [ ] `deployment` sidebar category\n249:   - [ ] Proper labels and descriptions for each category\n250: - [ ] Add cross-references in architecture pages:\n251:   - [ ] Router architecture → Go Client router endpoints link\n252:   - [ ] PicoD architecture → Python SDK code execution API link\n253:   - [ ] CRD architecture → Go Client CRUD operations link\n254: - [ ] Add cross-references in API pages:\n255:   - [ ] Client configuration → deployment configuration link\n256:   - [ ] API methods → Helm value configuration link\n257: - [ ] Create or update `docs/docs/intro.md` with:\n258:   - [ ] AgentCube overview\n259:   - [ ] Quick links to Getting Started, Architecture, API, Deployment\n260:   - [ ] Documentation structure diagram\n261: \n262: ---\n263: \n264: ## Phase 11: Quality Verification (REQ-011)\n265: \n266: - [ ] Verify Python SDK documentation coverage:\n267:   - [ ] All public methods in `CodeInterpreterClient` documented\n268:   - [ ] All public methods in `AgentRuntimeClient` documented\n269:   - [ ] Documentation coverage ≥90%\n270: - [ ] Build documentation without errors:\n271:   - [ ] Run `npm run build` in `docs/` directory\n272:   - [ ] Verify build succeeds with no errors\n273:   - [ ] Verify no broken internal links reported\n274: - [ ] Verify code examples:\n275:   - [ ] ≥80% code examples execute successfully\n276:   - [ ] Examples use realistic parameters\n277:   - [ ] Examples include necessary import statements\n278: - [ ] Verify formatting consistency:\n279:   - [ ] Headers use ATX style (# syntax)\n280:   - [ ] Code blocks have language annotations\n281:   - [ ] Tables use GitHub-flavored markdown\n282:   - [ ] Lists use consistent 2-space indentation\n283:   - [ ] Docusaurus frontmatter present where required\n284: \n285: ---\n286: \n287: ## Phase 12: Internationalization (REQ-012)\n288: \n289: - [ ] Verify English as primary documentation\n290: - [ ] Create `docs/i18n/` directory structure:\n291:   - [ ] `i18n/zh-CN/` for Chinese translation\n292:   - [ ] `i18n/ja/` for Japanese translation\n293:   - [ ] Translation JSON files for UI strings\n294: - [ ] Update `docs/docusaurus.config.ts` with:\n295:   - [ ] `defaultLocale: 'en'`\n296:   - [ ] `locales: ['en', 'zh-CN', 'ja']`\n297:   - [ ] Locale names and labels\n298:   - [ ] Locale switcher UI enabled\n299: \n300: ---\n301: \n302: ## Phase 13: Search Configuration (REQ-013)\n303: \n304: - [ ] Configure search plugin in `docs/docusaurus.config.ts`:\n305:   - [ ] Algolia DocSearch or local search plugin\n306:   - [ ] Search input visible in navbar\n307: - [ ] Verify search functionality:\n308:   - [ ] Search indexes architecture pages\n309:   - [ ] Search indexes API documentation\n310:   - [ ] Search indexes deployment guides\n311:   - [ ] Search indexes getting started pages\n312: - [ ] Verify API method searchability:\n313:   - [ ] \"execute_code\" returns Python SDK docs\n314:   - [ ] \"execute_code\" returns code execution flow docs\n315:   - [ ] \"execute_code\" returns quick start tutorial\n316: \n317: ---\n318: \n319: ## Summary\n320: \n321: | Phase | REQ | Tasks | Status |\n322: |-------|-----|-------|--------|\n323: | Phase 1 | REQ-001 | Architecture overview | Pending |\n324: | Phase 2 | REQ-002 | Component architecture (4 files) | Pending |\n325: | Phase 3 | REQ-003 | Data flow (3 files) | Pending |\n326: | Phase 4 | REQ-004 | Python SDK API (5 files) | Pending |\n327: | Phase 5 | REQ-005 | Go Client API (6 files) | Pending |\n328: | Phase 6 | REQ-006 | CRD Schema (2 files) | Pending |\n329: | Phase 7 | REQ-007 | Configuration (4 files) | Pending |\n330: | Phase 8 | REQ-008 | Deployment (4 files) | Pending |\n331: | Phase 9 | REQ-009 | Examples (4 files) | Pending |\n332: | Phase 10 | REQ-010 | Navigation & cross-references | Pending |\n333: | Phase 11 | REQ-011 | Quality verification | Pending |\n334: | Phase 12 | REQ-012 | Internationalization | Pending |\n335: | Phase 13 | REQ-013 | Search configuration | Pending |\n336: \n337: **Total Tasks:** ~75 atomic items  \n338: **Total Requirements:** 13  \n339: **Total Scenarios:** 48\n\n(End of file - total 339 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Tasks Checklist: AR-043 — 架构设计文档与 API 文档\n\n**Module:** docs  \n**Language:** Markdown  \n**Size:** M  \n**Stage:** ST-3 completed\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Architecture Overview (REQ-001)\n\n- [ ] Create `docs/docs/architecture/` directory structure\n- [ ] Create `docs/docs/architecture/overview.md` with:\n  - [ ] High-level system purpose and tech stack description\n  - [ ] ASCII or Mermaid component diagram showing system topology:\n    - Router ↔ Redis/Valkey ↔ WorkloadManager ↔ K8s API\n    - Sandbox Pods with PicoD daemon\n    - Agentd idle cleanup controller\n  - [ ] Tech stack table (Go 1.24, Python ≥3.10, Gin, K8s CRDs, Redis/Valkey, JWT RS256)\n  - [ ] Deployment topology section (Router, WorkloadManager, Sandbox Pods patterns)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/docs/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775907286698,"end":1775907286743}}}}
